content: I'll definitely take these resources and advice into consideration. I think I can start by taking on more leadership roles in my current projects and seeking feedback from my team members and mentors. I'll also look into the courses and books you recommended to improve my soft skills and business acumen. It's interesting that you mentioned letting go of technical tasks, as I've been doing a lot of hands-on work lately. I need to remind myself that as a leader, my role is to guide and direct, not to do everything myself. Thanks for the guidance! By the way, I was thinking about my background and how I've come a long way since graduating from UCLA. Do you think my educational background, including my Master's degree from Stanford, has played a significant role in my career success?
